Vintage-style illustration of a mechanical brass telescope connected to an intricate network of copper pipes and pneumatic tubes, reaching across a detailed antique map spread on a wooden desk. The telescope is pointed at a glowing orb containing swirling data streams represented as flowing ribbons of golden light. Around the desk, small clockwork automatons carry scrolls between ornate filing cabinets. The scene is bathed in warm sepia tones with rich amber and bronze highlights, evoking a Victorian-era inventor's workshop. Steam wisps curl from pipe joints while glass valves pulse with ethereal blue energy, suggesting the bridge between old mechanical systems and distant information sources.
